<br>
We did something similiar to this.  Used my mage to get wifey's druid to 60.  Once I got mod rods, wifey quad kited and then rested in treeform and used regens and mod rods to keep mana and HP going well.  She could quad 2.5 times faster than other druids nearby who had no help.  We did several of the 50s lvls in one easy day of fighting.  We actually did 59 when it was the true hell lvl in 4 days of on-and-off fighting.<br>
<br>
If you don't care to quad kite, a more frequently used method is to simply debuff the mob with Malosini, let the druid ENSNARE, ROOT, then DOT with Epic (if ya have it), Winged Death, and right click ES arms and then med.  Once the mob is under 50%, send pet in and kill it.  The pet should NOT need heals doing one mob at a time, since it heals so fast and should have some downtime between next mob.  While this is more efficient than a druid soloing with DoTs, it can be sped up if the druid does more than 1 mob at a time.<br>
<br>
For those who are truely adventurous (we did this for much of lvl 58 and 59), do this:<br>
<br>
Mage:<br>
  Summon your highest lvl WATER PET (need backstabbing),<br>
  Turn the pet's TAUNT OFF,<br>
  Keep the pet with the best burnout and best speed spell<br>
<br>
Druid:<br>
  Quad kite and after the mobs till each mob is BELOW 50%,<br>
  Run around and STAY WITHIN CLOSE AGGRO RANGE<br>
     This will keep the mobs facing YOU and OFF THE PET<br>
<br>
Mage:<br>
  Once mobs are below 50% HP, send the pet in to clean up<br>
  If done properly, the druid can nearly continuously quad kite<br>
<br>
Excluding some AE groups, this is the fastest exp possible in EQ from what I've seen.  This is nothing more than an Advanced Aggro Kite, however, the druids skills of kiting are seriously put to the test here.  If the druid gets out of aggro range, the mobs will turn on the pet.  If the pet's taunt is turned on, the mobs will turn on the pet - making backstab useless.<br>
<br>
You'll be amazed at the exp you can make doing this, but keep in mind if you're not very familiar with quad kiting and wanna try this, go find some green mobs to practice on and use small spells till you get the hang of it.<br>
<br>
Also remember that some zones are best to avoid when quading.  ME comes to mind.  General rule seems to be, train me, I train you...personally, I kinda like hunting near the zonelines cause trains happen about every 10 minutes it seems and it's possible to grab a train that's already damaged and snared and finish the job for all the exp if the original quader zones.<br>
<br>
Work smarter, not harder. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill>The Hunt</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
